Elon Musk is forced to leave the post of the head of the board of directors of Tesla
The US Securities and Exchange Commission and Tesla founder Elon Musk have settled their fraud dispute.
It is reported by CNBC News.
According to the TV channel, as part of the agreements reached, Musk will have to leave the post of head of the Tesla board of directors.
At the same time, the commission allowed Musk to retain the post of head of Tesla.
As noted, the Tesla founder will also have to pay an administrative fine of $ 20 million.
Tesla will be charged the same amount.
In this case, the money will be distributed among the affected investors.
In addition, the company must appoint two independent directors.
Elon Musk is an American entrepreneur, one of the 50 richest people in the world according to Forbes magazine.
He is the chief executive officer of space corporation SpaceX, the neurotech company Neuralink, and the developer of Tesla electric vehicles, as well as co-founder of Paypal.
The US Securities and Exchange Commission has previously sued Tesla CEO Elon Musk over his tweet about a possible buyout of the company.
Last month, Musk announced plans to take Tesla into a private company and buy back all shares on the exchange for a fixed price of $ 420.
The share price at $ 420 was allegedly set &quot;because of the significance of this number in the culture of marijuana,&quot; Bloomberg previously reported, citing co-director of the Commission&#39;s security department Stephen Peikin.
At the same time, Elon Musk subsequently abandoned his plans to buy back the shares.
Commenting on the lawsuit filed against him by the US Securities and Exchange Commission, the businessman said that he considered the fraud charges unfounded, and added that he was very disappointed and saddened by these claims.
&quot;Honesty is the most important value in my life, and the facts will prove that I have not violated it in any way,&quot; the businessman told CNBC.
At the same time, in August, a group of Tesla shareholders filed a class action lawsuit against Musk, complaining about financial losses incurred.
The plaintiffs argued that the positions of the businessman brought them losses.
In particular, one of the shareholders said that the businessman&#39;s tweets were misleading, because of which the sellers of Tesla shares were forced to buy securities at artificially inflated prices in order to cover their positions.
Also, other plaintiffs noted that Elon Musk&#39;s careless statements led to sharp fluctuations in the exchange rate.
In September, Elon Musk was also accused of stock fraud by the head of the research company Citron Research.
Meanwhile, if Musk could not resolve his dispute with the US Securities and Exchange Commission, he would face dismissal from the management of the company and even jail.
This, in particular, was announced to CNBC by the former chairman of the commission Harvey Pitt.
Musk is &quot;a nice guy who doesn&#39;t know how to run a car company.&quot;
