The accusation for the Dagestani deputy became news
The Sovetsky District Court of Makhachkala imprisoned for two months a deputy of the People&#39;s Assembly of Dagestan, Rajab Abdulatipov, who was suspected of participating in a criminal community that formalized disability in exchange for bribes.
Kommersant learned the details of the investigation materials, shedding light on how exactly, according to the Russian Investigative Committee, the younger brother of the former head of the republic, Ramazan Abdulatipov, Rajab Abdulatipov, contributed to the criminal actions of the now former head of the Main Bureau of Medical and Social Expertise Magomed Makhachev and his accomplices ...
Among other things, during the operational-search activities carried out by the Ministry of Internal Affairs, it was established that Rajab Abdulatipov lobbied for the appointment of Magomed Makhachev as head of the bureau, allegedly receiving 70 million rubles for this.
We will remind that earlier the investigation against Magomed Makhachev, other heads and employees of the territorial bureaus of medical and social expertise, which are in his subordination, initiated a criminal case under Art. 210 (creation of a criminal community with the use of official position and participation in it), art. 290 (taking a bribe by an organized group), Art. 292 (official forgery) and Art. 159 (fraud on an especially large scale) of the Criminal Code of the Russian Federation.
As follows from the materials of the investigation, at the end of 2013, Rajab Abdulatipov, knowing about the illegal actions of Magomed Makhachev and his accomplices, who were involved in the theft of funds from the Pension Fund, joined their activities by joining a criminal community.
Being the head of the department of the Federal Migration Service of Russia for Dagestan and having connections in state authorities and law enforcement structures, as well as using his family relationship with the head of Dagestan, Rajab Abdulatipov, the investigators believe, “ensured the activities of other members of the criminal community, established contacts with officials persons of state bodies to support the illegal activities of Magomed Makhachev and his appointment as head of the federal government institution &quot;Main Bureau of Medical and Social Expertise in the Republic of Dagestan&quot;, organized the illegal establishment of disabilities for citizens. &quot;
After the announcement of this information at a meeting of the Soviet District Court on Friday, Rajab Abdulatipov denied the charges against him.
&quot;Of course, everything that is being brought against me today is new for me, I am absolutely not familiar with this,&quot; he said.
The court arrested the United Russia deputy not for ten days before being charged, as was the case with the previous high-ranking Dagestani officials, but for two months at once, since his case includes Art. 210 of the Criminal Code of the Russian Federation.
